TOOL_USE: Write({"file_path": "/home/joe/Documents/repo/skill/sci-draw/.claude/_eval_sandbox_home/.claude/plans/swirling-scribbling-tide.md", "content": "# Neural Network Architecture Diagram — LSTM with Skip Connections\n\n## Context\n\nUser needs a publication-quality neural network architecture diagram showing:\n- Input: 256-dim embedding\n- Three LSTM hidden layers: 128-dim → 64-dim → 32-dim\n- Softmax output layer\n- Skip connections between layers\n- Dropout rate annotations\n\n## Design\n\n### Figure Spec\n\n| Item        | Value |\n|-------------|-------|\n| Conclusion  | Schematic illustration of a stacked LSTM classifier with residual skip connections, showing dimensional progression and regularization. |\n| Evidence logic | Each layer is a labeled block; forward arrows show data flow; curved skip arrows show residual paths; dropout rates annotated between layers. |\n| Format       | PDF + PNG, vector-first, 300 dpi fallback |\n| Style       | Modern clean scientific — flat colored blocks, no 3D/shadows, consistent spacing |\n\n### Layout (left → right)\n\n```\n[Input Embedding] ──forward──→ [LSTM 1] ──forward──→ [LSTM 2] ──forward──→ [LSTM 3] ──forward──→ [Softmax]\n     256                       128                      64                      32                    Output\n        │                        │                        │\n        └── skip ────────────────→                        │\n        │                        └── skip ────────────────→\n      Dropout                    Dropout                  Dropout\n```\n\n### Color Scheme\n- Input block: light blue\n- LSTM blocks: light orange/salmon\n- Softmax block: light green\n- Forward arrows: dark gray\n- Skip arrows: red/dashed\n- Dropout text: red, placed above/below forward arrows\n\n### Layers & Labels\n\n| Block | Position (x) | Color | Label |\n|-------|-------------|-------|-------|\n| Input Embedding (256) | x=0 | blue | \"Input Embedding\\n(256-dim)\" |\n| LSTM Layer 1 (128) | x=1 | orange | \"LSTM Layer 1\\n(128 units)\" |\n| LSTM Layer 2 (64) | x=2 | orange | \"LSTM Layer 2\\n(64 units)\" |\n| LSTM Layer 3 (32) | x=3 | orange | \"LSTM Layer 3\\n(32 units)\" |\n| Softmax Output | x=4 | green | \"Softmax\\nOutput\" |\n\n### Annotations\n- Forward arrows between consecutive layers\n- Skip arrows: Input→LSTM2, LSTM1→LSTM3 (dashed, curved below blocks)\n- Dropout rates (e.g., 0.3, 0.4, 0.5) between layers, above or below arrows\n\n## Implementation\n\n**Tool:** Python + matplotlib, single script\n\n### Script Structure\n1. Create figure with `plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))`\n2. Define layer blocks as `FancyBboxPatch` rectangles with consistent size\n3. Draw forward connections as `FancyArrowPatch`\n4. Draw skip connections as curved `ConnectionPatch` with dashed style\n5. Add text labels for layer names, dimensions, dropout rates\n6. Add legend for line types (forward, skip)\n7. Export as PDF + PNG\n\n### Key matplotlib objects\n- `matplotlib.patches.FancyBboxPatch` — rounded rectangle blocks\n- `matplotlib.patches.FancyArrowPatch` — forward arrows\n- `matplotlib.patches.Arc` or `ConnectionPatch` with `connectionstyle=\"arc3,rad=-0.3\"` — curved skip connections\n- `ax.text()` / `ax.annotate()` — labels\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Run `python draw_nn_arch.py`\n2. Check output PDF and PNG render correctly\n3. Verify: all 5 blocks present, 4 forward connections, 2 skip connections, dropout labels visible\n4. Check colors and fonts are publication-grade\n\n## Output Files\n\n- `nn_architecture.pdf`\n- `nn_architecture.png`\n"})
